      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoI (relative hemolysis index RH) directly maps to the clinical decision criterion for CPB device comparison.",
      "rationale": "The relative hemolysis index RH = NIH_device / NIH_predicate is the primary QoI and directly supports the regulatory comparison criterion RH < 1. This QoI is mechanistically linked to erythrocyte damage mechanisms captured by the power-law hemolysis model."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
